title: For Sale:  GG&G XDS Bipod For Sale
postcontent:
This Bipod is almost brand new.  I put it on my rifle and found that it is too high for me to shoot off of a bench rest comfortably.  Below is the official description from GGGAZ.com  I paid $211.27, but will let go for $180.  I will even pay to have it shipped via USPS flat rate.  In the pictures, it looks like there are scuffs on the legs, but it is only dust.  I can send you new pictures to prove it if you are interested.

The GG&G Heavy Duty XDS Bipod is perfect for those heavier weapons like the M-14 and AR-30. It offers a greater range of rifle cant than our earlier models. In addition to a much stronger pivot mechanism, the new design affords 25 degrees of cant in either direction of center. Not only does this increase better rough terrain adjustability, but this pivoting capability allows the deployed bipod leg to be used as a vertical foregrip if required for rapid transition. In addition, a tension mechanism and adjustment knob has been added so that the operator does not need tools to make tension adjustments to the swivel.

The GG&G Heavy Duty XDS Tactical Bipod is specifically designed and manufactured to meet current military requirements. The Heavy Duty Bipod is exceptionally rugged; it will not only withstand extreme environmental conditions from -55 degrees Fahrenheit to +155 degrees Fahrenheit, but will be operational under those conditions.

Manufactured from aircraft grade 6061 T6 aluminum alloy with extreme duty connection points and fasteners, this swiveling bipod for the M14, AR-10 and other large caliber rifles and carbines is still remarkably lightweight at only 17 oz.

Features include a 8" to 10.5" height adjustment when measured from the dovetail attachment, silent deployment, fully adjustable legs with thumbnut adjustments, and grip tight foot pads. All aluminum parts are bead blasted and Type III hard coat anodized per mil-spec in a non reflective matte black combat finish. The bipod is equipped with a MIL-STD-1913 rail adapter that does not require tools for installation. The Heavy Duty Bipod will also attach to any rifle with a 6 o'clock under barrel MIL-STD-1913 or Weaver type rail.

title: For Sale:  Colt Single Action Army Revolver SAA Gold, Frontier Six Shooter, Ivory Grips c.1925, Cased
postcontent:
This is a unique and extremely rare Colt Single Action Army revolver, in .44-40 caliber, which is factory gold plated with factory ivory grips, made in 1925 (serial #347526). It was originally shipped to G. W. Shroyer and Company, Dayton, Ohio, May 16, 25, as a blue and case colored .32-20 with 7.5 barrel. It was returned to the Colt plant sometime between then and 1937, when it was changed to a Frontier Six Shooter (.44-40) with 5.5 barrel, ivory grips with medallions, and gold plated, as evidenced by the Colt rework & (ampersand) mark on the right rear of the trigger guard. It appears unfired since the factory rework.

As Kopec states in his book (p. 169, 1976 edition),  in most parts of the world the SAs hard working days were over, and  a number of its sales after 1923 were intended as gifts, presentations, prizes or just to rekindle memories of the good old days. This Colt typifies guns of that nature, remaining in 95% plus condition, with only the gold having been rubbed off in spots. The nickel finish, where the gold is missing, is almost perfect (gold plated guns had to be nickel plated before the gold would adhere).

This fine Colt has been custom cased in a late 1800s lap desk, made of hardwoods and intricate inlaid veneers. It comes with the revolvers accessories as well as antique pen, nibs and brass ink well holders. The case also has its key and locks.

title: For Sale:   RARE NIB DAN WESSON 715 HV6 .357 MAGNUM 2014 PRE-PRODUCTION
postcontent:
Brand new in the box

Manufacturer: Dan Wesson (CZ-USA)

Model: 715

Caliber: .357 Magnum/.38 Special

Capacity: 6 Round Cylinder

Barrel: 6" Heavy with Ventilated Rib

These are NEW for 2014 limited run, Pre-Production 715 revolvers from Dan Wesson



Returning to regular production late summer 2014, the 715 is as it was before -- designed and built to be the most accurate, rugged and versatile revolver on the market. Shipped with a 6" barrel, the new shroud is designated the HV6, a heavy vent shroud profile that tames the .357's recoil very well.

The double action trigger is short and relatively light, while the single action is light and crisp. The target-like SA trigger pull made the Dan Wesson revolver a favorite among competitors and hunters, and the tradition continues in the 715.

Barrel assemblies and grips are easily swapped by the shooter, and the 715 accepts grips and barrel/shroud assemblies from 15-2 model and newer revolvers.

The original Dan Wesson revolver improved on the accuracy and service life of the traditional double action revolver design in a few ways. The tensioned barrel of the DW interchangeable barrel system enhances accuracy, pulling the barrel tight like a guitar string, enabling it to vibrate at the same frequency every time. The forward crane latch, located in front of the cylinder and paired with a rear ball detent helps to ensure proper cylinder/barrel alignment during firing. Superior to the rear locking designs of other revolvers, it adds to the accuracy of the 715.

While the tensioned barrel definitely improves accuracy above other revolvers, it's the consistent cylinder/barrel alignment that contributes most to the accuracy of the design.

Additionally, the clockwise-rotating cylinder reduces stress on the crane, since it turns in the same direction the crane locks, prolonging service life and keeping everything tight. The 715's frame is robust, built to handle the heaviest of factory loads.

title: For Sale:  Type 53 Chinese Carbine (Mosin Nagant M44)
postcontent:
This is a collectible original condition 1956 Chinese Type 53 carbine.  The Type 53 is the Chinese version of the Russian Mosin-Nagant M44.  They are a blast to shoot!  It has a 20" barrel, original hardwood stock that is worn with little of the original shellac but still beautiful, excellent bluing, and the original folding spike bayonet.  The numbers stamped on the receiver, magazine floorplate, buttplate and etched on the stock below the buttplate (unusual) all match.  The bolt SN does not match but has the interesting characteristic of having an Izhevsk (Russian arsenal, vertical arrow inside a triangle) stamp and has a serial number consisting of 2 Cyrillic characters followed by 4 numbers in the style of the M44.  

I have checked headspace with a field gauge and it passed.  The measured average trigger pull is 5 lbs 6 oz, which is considerably lighter than the average Russian Mosin Nagant rifle.  Trigger is smooth rather than gritty as is often the case for Mosin Nagants.  The rifle has been thoroughly cleaned of Cosmoline preservative and is in overall "very good" NRA military surplus condition.  I have shot this carbine and it performs very well.

I originally acquired this rifle with my C&R license, so I will need to see a valid drivers license or government issued picture ID for a transfer.  No out of state buyers, unless you want to pay for shipping to your FFL and transfer fees.  Interstate transfers require the involvement of an FFL.
